<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14107">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Geocaching.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
      Additional educational resources are available on our
      <a
        href="https://www.scouting.org/skills/merit-badges/counselor-information/"
        target="_blank"
        ><b>Counselor Information Page.</b></a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8577">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8577 mb-requirement-id-8578">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        while participating in geocaching activities, and what you should do to
        anticipate, help prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://geocachingtoday.com/geocaching-safety-tips-to-stay-safe-while-treasure-hunting/"
          target="_blank"
          >GeoCaching Safety: 12 Critical Tips to Stay Safe While Treasure
          Hunting (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YGQG0C0HBGw" target="_blank"
          >Surviving the Wild—Essential Hiking Safety Tips (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8577 mb-requirement-id-8579">
        (b) Discuss first aid and prevention for the types of injuries or
        illnesses that could occur while participating in geocaching activities,
        including cuts, scrapes, snakebite, insect stings, tick bites, exposure
        to poisonous plants, heat and cold reactions (sunburn, heatstroke, heat
        exhaustion, hypothermia), and dehydration. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/nxExCQiWa_U" target="_blank"
          >Backpacking First Aid (What To Carry + Foot Care, Snakes, Poison
          Plants, Hypothermia, etc) (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8577 mb-requirement-id-8580">
        (c) Discuss how to properly plan an activity that uses GPS, including
        using the buddy system, sharing your plan with others, and considering
        the weather, route, and proper attire. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/0_wubfWGADo" target="_blank"
          >Geocaching Tips and Tricks (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8581">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Discuss the following with your counselor:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8581 mb-requirement-id-8582">
        (a) Why you should never bury a cache <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.geocaching.com/help/index.php?pg=kb.chapter&amp;id=128&amp;pgid=905"
          target="_blank"
          >Don't Bury Your Cache or Attach It to a Tree (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8581 mb-requirement-id-8583">
        (b) How to use proper geocaching etiquette when hiding or seeking a
        cache, and how to properly hide, post, maintain, and dismantle a
        geocache <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GXzIu7p82jg" target="_blank"
          >Geocaching Etiquette (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8581 mb-requirement-id-8584">
        (c) The Leave No Trace Seven Principles and the Outdoor Code as they
        apply to geocaching <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-OBCyHbYmmA" target="_blank"
          >How To Geocache the Leave No Trace Way (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8595">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Explain the following terms used in geocaching: waypoint, log, cache,
      accuracy, difficulty and terrain ratings, attributes, and trackable.
      Choose five additional terms to explain to your counselor. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a
        href="https://www.hoagiesgifted.org/geocaching_acronyms.htm"
        target="_blank"
        >Geocaching Acronyms and Terms (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.geocaching.com/about/glossary.aspx" target="_blank"
        >Geocaching Terms (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8596">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Explain how the Global Positioning System (GPS) works. Then, using
      Scouting's EDGE, demonstrate to your counselor the use of a GPS unit.
      Include marking and editing a waypoint, changing field functions, and
      changing the coordinate system in the unit. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/jl2xQk-z4To" target="_blank"
        >How Does GPS Find Your Location (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/RNhtn71k-wA" target="_blank"
        >How To Use a Garmin eTrex 10 GPS Receiver (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8585">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8585 mb-requirement-id-8586">
        (a) Show you know how to use a map and compass and explain why this is
        important for geocaching. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7MQUIYsmQhc" target="_blank"
          >Compass 101 (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qGqLuqnvROg" target="_blank"
          >THIS Is How To Use a Compass and Map (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8585 mb-requirement-id-8587">
        (b) Explain the similarities and differences between GPS navigation and
        standard map-reading skills and describe the benefits of each. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/mK3pOU_x4jQ" target="_blank"
          >Using a GPS with a Map and Compass (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8597">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Describe to your counselor the four steps to finding your first cache.
      Then mark and edit a waypoint. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/7LvnVdaw5sM" target="_blank"
        >10 Things To Do When Playing Geocaching (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8598">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      With your parent or guardian's permission, go to www.geocaching.com. Type
      in your city and state to locate public geocaches in your area. Share with
      your counselor the posted information about three of those geocaches.
      Then, pick one of the three and find the cache.<br /><br /><b>Note: </b>To
      fulfill this requirement, you will need to set up a free user account with
      www.Geocaching.com. Before doing so, ask your parent for permission and
      help. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://www.geocaching.com/play" target="_blank"
        >Geocaching.com (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/-ddhwGsGDjs" target="_blank"
        >How To Find Your First Geocache! (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8590">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8590 mb-requirement-id-8591">
        (a) If a Cache to Eagle® series exists in your council, visit at least
        three of the locations in the series. Describe the projects that each
        cache you visit highlights, and explain how the Cache to Eagle® program
        helps share our Scouting service with the public. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://blog.scoutingmagazine.org/2021/02/12/she-created-a-geocaching-trail-that-links-together-14-eagle-scout-service-projects"
          target="_blank"
          >She Created a Geocaching Trail That Links Together 14 Eagle Scout
          Service Projects (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8590 mb-requirement-id-8592">
        (b) Create a Scouting-related Travel Bug® that promotes one of the
        values of Scouting. Release your Travel Bug into a public geocache and,
        with your parent or guardian's permission, monitor its progress at
        www.geocaching.com for 30 days. Keep a log, and share this with your
        counselor at the end of the 30-day period. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Fwl8-pvwHJQ" target="_blank"
          >What Is a Travel Bug in Geocaching (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8590 mb-requirement-id-8593">
        (c) Set up and hide a public geocache, following the guidelines in the
        <em>Geocaching</em> merit badge pamphlet. Before doing so, share with
        your counselor a three-month maintenance plan for the geocache where you
        are personally responsible for those three months. After setting up the
        geocache, with your parent or guardian's permission, follow the logs
        online for 30 days and share them with your counselor. You must archive
        the geocache when you are no longer maintaining it. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/0018rkb_knA" target="_blank"
          >What To Do (and NOT Do) When Hiding a Geocache (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8590 mb-requirement-id-8594">
        (d) Explain what Cache In Trash Out (CITO) means, and describe how you
        have practiced CITO at public geocaches or at a CITO event. Then, either
        create CITO containers to leave at public caches, or host a CITO event
        for your unit or for the public. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/5eIwxTAaxKw" target="_blank"
          >Cache In Cache Out Geocaching Events (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Brhs9gpCszE" target="_blank"
          >Geocaching Capital of Canada Cleanup (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.geocaching.com/help/index.php?pg=kb.chapter&amp;id=23&amp;pgid=799"
          target="_blank"
          >Event Caches (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8599">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Plan a geohunt for a youth group such as your troop or a neighboring pack,
      at school, or your place of worship. Choose a theme, set up a course with
      at least four waypoints, teach the players how to use a GPS unit, and play
      the game. Tell your counselor about your experience, and share the
      materials you used and developed for this event. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/y69n3o3SAEA" target="_blank"
        >Geocaching—Setting up the Experience (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
